BOIL water and wine in a large skillet; add salmon. Reduce heat to low; cover. Cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until thickest part of salmon flakes easily when tested with a fork. PREPARE pasta according to package directions. Toss pasta with carrot and parsley; divide among plates. Top with salmon. Spoon sauce over each serving; garnish with dill. Season with salt and ground black pepper.